x=a(\cos \theta + \theta \sin \theta) 
 y=a(\sin \theta- \theta \cos \theta) 
\frac{d^2y}{dx^2}= \frac{\sec^3 \theta}{a \theta}
\frac{\frac{d}{d \theta} \frac{ \cos \theta + \theta \sin \theta}{\theta \cos \theta - \sin \theta}}{\frac{dx}{d \theta}}=\frac{1+\theta^2}{a(\theta \cos \theta- \sin \theta)}
\large\frac{d^2y}{dx^2}=\frac{d}{dx}(\frac{dy}{dx})=\frac{d}{d\theta}(\frac{dy}{dx})\times\frac{d\theta}{dx}=\frac{\frac{d}{d\theta}(\frac{dy}{dx})}{\frac{dx}{d\theta}}
\large\frac{dy}{dx}=\frac{\frac{dy}{d\theta}}{\frac{dx}{d\theta}}
